  "prompt": "What does \"subject to availability\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Subject to availability\" is a phrase often used in marketing and sales to indicate that a product, service, or offer may not be guaranteed and could be limited in quantity or time. It means that the customer may only be able to obtain the item or service if it is currently in stock or accessible at that moment. Essentially, it serves as a disclaimer that the offer could change or be withdrawn based on supply or demand conditions. For example, a hotel might advertise a special rate \"subject to availability,\" meaning that the rate may only apply if there are still rooms available at that price at the time of booking.",
